## Examples

### Mac-only (no stepping)

```markdown
## Windows machines

**Required now:** Nothing. This change only affects tests on macOS CI.

**When it matters:** Build VM sync first, then transfer to print-test PC for physical prints.
```

### Active handoff — first step after push (build VM)

```markdown
## What to do on your build VM (Windows)

**Step 1** — Open PowerShell in the repo folder and pull the branch the agent pushed.

```powershell
cd C:\Users\Deon\event-platform-print-relay-windows
git fetch origin
git checkout feature/sprint-1-m1
git pull origin feature/sprint-1-m1
```

**Report back:** Paste the output of `git log -1 --oneline` (we will confirm it matches the agent’s commit).
```

### Physical print sign-off — print-test PC

```markdown
## What to do on your print-test PC (Windows)

**Step 1** — Run the relay from the folder you extracted from the build VM zip.

1. Double-click `C:\PrintRelay\EventPlatform.PrintRelay.exe` (or your extract path).
2. Confirm the tray icon appears (click **^** near the clock if hidden).

**Report back:** Does the tray icon appear? Is Status checklist green?
```

### Bug retest — one action (usually print-test PC)

```markdown
## What to do on your print-test PC (Windows)

**Step 1** — Reproduce the bug.

1. Right-click the Print Relay tray icon (near the clock; click **^** if hidden).
2. Click **Copy diagnostics**.

**Report back:** Did you get a balloon tip saying copied, or the STA error dialog? Paste the exact error text if any.
```
